name: isopropyl acetate
Reason: 1-ethylpiperazine-2,3-dione has a melting point around 106°C. The basic unit for our comparison will be ethanol, which has a melting point of -114.1 degrees Celsius. The introduction of the methyl group (–CH3) in place of a hydrogen atom increases the molecular weight and size which generally raises the melting point. The methyl group also introduces a new hydrogen bonding potential, which can further contribute to the melting point. The net effect should thus be a raised melting point due to both molecular size and hydrogen bonding.
